 {"id":"beads_rust-19my.3","title":"Fix ntm bulk-assign to work with all agent types","description":"## Context
Part of ntm #23 fix. `ntm --robot-bulk-assign` returns empty assignments despite valid tasks and agents.

## Dependency
This likely depends on fixing Codex state detection (beads_rust-19my.2). If ntm can't detect agent state, it can't determine which agents are idle and eligible for assignment.

## Current Behavior
```bash
$ ntm --robot-bulk-assign=all2down --from-bv
{
  "assignments": [],
  "unassigned_panes": [1, 2, 3, 4, 6]
}
```
- `bv --robot-next` returns valid tasks
- Agents are running in panes 1,2,3,4,6
- But no assignments are made

## Investigation Plan
1. Find bulk-assign logic (likely `internal/robot/assign.go` or `cmd/robot.go`)
2. Trace the assignment algorithm:
   a. How does it get available tasks? (from bv)
   b. How does it determine agent eligibility? (state detection)
   c. What conditions prevent assignment?
3. Add debug logging to identify where assignments fail

## Likely Fix
Once Codex detection works (beads_rust-19my.2), bulk-assign should work. But may also need:
- Better fallback behavior when state is UNKNOWN
- Configuration for "assign even if state unclear"
- Logging to explain why assignments weren't made

